<br>
The problem, as i see it, is with guilds 1-2, 3-4-5-6, 7-8-9, and  so on. (btw all 9 guilds in this example are  90 percent or  more all level 60's the top 6 being  all 60+aa)<br>
<br>
Like say guild 1-2  are in VT,  guilds 3-4-5-6 can easily kill Velious ubers and many Luclin  up to SSra. <br>
<br>
Guild 7-8-9 can just  do velious ubers/NToV/lower luclin named, but never get the chance becuase  all of the above guilds never move on.  They continue to kill  the new stuff and old too. Only they kill it faster.  On The Nameless even the Top guilds still wack King T or Dain or AoW,  if they are up. Along with the rest of the top 6 guilds on the serever that can kill easily.  Shoot Everything of  worth usually  dies  on patch day within hours. (Minutes of the mob spawning)<br>
<br>
This has forced many, that are not in the top, to become frustrated and leave EQ. Something i am considering. People say well join other guild_001 or guild_002, well that is not possible as their membership requirements are geared to people who have played for ever, or were Powerlelveled/Twinked by their friends in these guilds. <br>
<br>
This is just   the way I see things  at the High End  game  a place where you can not rise to any more. You have to  be in &quot;the club&quot; or  have  freinds in &quot;the club&quot; to invite you into &quot;the club&quot; to move on. You have to get all you can. Then join a guild already there or rarely  have the opertunity to advance any farther.<br>
<br>
I may be one of the  first people  to buy EQ2  simply to be there  for the long haul. <p><center>
