<br>
I can't remember the last time anyone went to Thurg for the Dain.  Sure the belt is still great but it certainly is not a big enough draw to bring everyone over (and fewer people have the faction or desire to camp out in Kael waiting for KT for the turn-in).  KT is another matter, that is a pretty good loot pool still and a ST key never hurts.  AoW is another again, a fun fight and a great loot pool.  Yelli has those gloves and a key and would certainly die if found up.<br>
<br>
None of those are first targets for guilds that can kill stronger though.  On patch day the desire is to log on, figure out what Remedy didn't kill that is still up and go from there (while also finding out where LoS is).  In terms of priority it is definitely anything in Ssra first, perhaps Shei after that.  Burrower if there or even CT if nothing else is around.  First Brood Dragons are worth heading for also and ST would be a target on occasion also I am sure.  Seru isn't being contested much as far as I know, so he can wait.<br>
<br>
I see the way things are as more of a comment on the slowness of loot dropping.  With 50+ members showing up for raids, a guild needs to do a huge number of Mob X kills to outfit the members in the loot that he drops.  In some cases (Cursed, HP, AL etc) there are so many strong rare drops that no guild will be 'done' with them anytime soon.  PoP will change priorities of course but upper-tier guilds will still head back to earlier Mobs to some degree of course, for ST keys if nothing else. <p><center><b><font color=RED><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=78504>Celeris Tujimson</a><br>Assassin of The Nameless<br>
